cisc187.util

Interface Queue<E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue

    public interface Queue<E>
extends java.lang.Iterable<E>
    An interface that specifies the familiar queue abstraction, but with limited capacity.

    In addition to the methods required in the definition of this interface, a class implementing this interface should provide a public constructor with a single argument of type int, which specifies the capacity of the Queue. The constructor should throw an IllegalArgumentException if the specified capacity is negative.

      • enqueue

        void enqueue(E e)
        Adds the specified element to the tail of this Queue.
        PRECONDITION: the Queue's size is less than its capacity.
        POSTCONDITION: the element is now the tail element in this Queue, none of the other elements have been changed, and the size is increased by 1.
        Parameters:
        e - the element to add to the queue
        Throws:
        FullQueueException - if the Queue is at capacity.

      • dequeue

        E dequeue()
        Removes the element at the head of this Queue. Returns the element removed, or null if there was no such element.
        PRECONDITION: the Queue's size is greater than zero.
        POSTCONDITION: the head element in this Queue has been removed, none of the other elements have been changed, and the size is decreased by 1.
        Returns:
        the element removed, or null if the queue is empty.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - if the Queue is already empty.

      • peek

        E peek()
        Returns the element at the head of this Queue, or null if there was no such element.
        PRECONDITION: the Queue's size is greater than zero.
        POSTCONDITION: The Queue is unchanged.
        Returns:
        the element at the head, or null if the size was zero.
